headline: CPB Q3 Deep Dive: Brand Investment and Cost Pressures Shape Quarterly Results
summary: Packaged food company Campbell's (NASDAQ:CPB) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 3.4% year on year to $2.68 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.77 per share was 5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
